Crowd Source collection holds around 150 photographs taken with the first 'secret' Detective Camera . 
  Arthur Syer was a 27-year-old man living in Sydney who took advantage of the first hand held camera . 
  The photographs will go on display at the State Library on Saturday . 
  The detective camera was produced between 1883 and 1887 . 
  It was the first time people were able to take a photograph without their subjects knowing . 
  The photos were a 'real revolution and turning point in photography'